Package: pwndoc-mcp-server
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: MCP Server for PwnDoc - Pentest Documentation Integration
 A Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that provides seamless integration
 between AI assistants (Claude, OpenAI) and PwnDoc, the pentest reporting
 and documentation platform.
 .
 Features:
  - 50+ tools for audit, finding, client, and vulnerability management
  - Natural language queries for penetration testing data
  - Full PwnDoc API coverage with authentication handling
  - Rate limiting, auto-retry, and comprehensive error management
  - Support for stdio and SSE transports
 .
 This package provides a standalone binary that requires no Python runtime.
